OL,6,FNorthern Ireland is the only part of
OL,7,Fthe United Kingdom that doesn't have a
OL,8,FMother and Baby Unit (MBU), which
OL,9,Fprovides specialist inpatient care for
OL,10,Fmums experiencing severe postnatal
OL,11,Fillness and their babies.
OL,13,FInstead, mothers are admitted to
OL,14,Fgeneral acute psychiatric wards for
OL,15,Fnon-specialist treatment, separating
OL,16,Fthem from babies.
OL,18,FOne in five women will experience
OL,19,Fmental health problems during
OL,20,Fpregnancy or after birth.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/7
