OL,6,FAround 1,000 women each year in
OL,7,FNorthern Ireland will develop a severe
OL,8,Fpostnatal illness. This can include
OL,9,Fpostpartum psychosis, severe
OL,10,Fdepression and anxiety, and obsessive
OL,11,Fcompulsive disorder.
OL,13,FBetween 84 and 122 will need admission
OL,14,Fto hospital. Suicide is the leading
OL,15,Fcause of maternal death, but with the
OL,16,Fright care it is almost always
OL,17,Fpreventable.
OL,19,FThe cost of setting up the unit is
OL,20,Festimated to be #10m.
